  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\nWhen the user presses the *Pending contact requests* section, the Activity Center should be opened in the *Contact Requests* tab and with the unread filter enabled.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/208510427-daf56acc-cbe8-42bf-b171-44991ee91541.png\" width=\"400\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/208512927-5e7fb921-3a0e-4fc0-921b-d54e56a67d38.png\" \r\n width=\"400\"/>\r\n\r\n### Shouldn't we use the current design?\r\n\r\nThe current design specifies that when the user presses the *Pending contact requests* section they should see a bottom sheet, fully featured to manage the requests. This is currently implemented in production code, but it's buggy (UI and behavior) and it's duplicating most of the features already available in the Activity Center.\r\n\r\nInstead of fixing the issues, designers and engineers agreed to simply reuse the Activity Center **until the dogfooding of the new mobile app stabilizes**. This will give us more time to work on other important issues. In the future (probably around late Feb/2023 or later), we can reevaluate this feature, therefore it's only temporarily deprioritized @xAlisher, @pedro-et\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/208511056-6077683d-3267-47ba-80cf-d1e4944e7ded.png)\r\n\r\n### Resources\r\n\r\n- Current design in [Figma - Messages for Mobile](https://www.figma.com/file/7KIYbhoqNGAIFonE0w9TDz/Messages-for-Mobile?node-id=2010%3A507764&t=cguAmdcNZy7qazwk-0).\r\n",
